\title{separating family for a category}
\taxon{definition}

\import{base-macros}


\p{Given an ordinary category #{E}, a set-indexed family #{\prn{s\Sub{i}}\Sub{i\in I}} of #{E}-objects is called a \em{small separating family} for #{E} when, assuming that for all #{i\in I} and all #{\Mor{u}{s_i}{x}} we have #{u;f=u;g}, we then have #{f=g}.}